      "comment_id" : 134372334,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I agree that using Lombok is a great way to generate getters, setters, equals, hash code, and constructors without having to write a lot of boilerplate code in your class. By using Lombok, you can reduce the amount of repetitive code in your project, making it more concise and easier to maintain. Additionally, Lombok can save you a lot of time and effort, allowing you to focus on the more important aspects of your code, such as business logic and algorithmic design."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 258983,
      "reputation" : 1597,
      "user_id" : 541526,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8f298284129135a1309ea3521ac2fbe0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "dongpf",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/541526/dongpf"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 57,
    "last_activity_date" : 1455762987,
    "last_edit_date" : 1455762987,
    "creation_date" : 1455761253,
    "answer_id" : 35471477,
    "question_id" : 7221691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>All the other answers are just focus on the IDE level, these are not the most effective and elegant way to generate getters and setters.</strong> \nIf you have tens of attributes, the relevant getters and setters methods will make your class code very verbose.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The best way I ever used to generate getters and setters automatically is using project lombok annotations in your java project</strong>, lombok.jar will generate getter and setter method when you compile java code. </p>\n\n<p>You just focus on class attributes/variables naming and definition, lombok will do the rest. This is easy to maintain your code. </p>\n\n<p>For example, if you want to add getter and setter method for <code>age</code> variable, you just add two lombok annotations:\n</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Getter @Setter \npublic int age = 10;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This is equal to code like that:</p>\n\n<pre><code>private int age = 10;\npublic int getAge() {\n    return age;\n}\npublic void setAge(int age) {\n    this.age = age;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can find more details about lombok here: <a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/\">Project Lombok</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8247631,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 6203235,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f20d887a9e3ded50a5adf043fe7a519d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "abhinav",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6203235/abhinav"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1460627460,
    "creation_date" : 1460627460,
    "answer_id" : 36619501,
    "question_id" : 7221691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>**In Eclipse Ide</p>\n\n<p>for generating both setters and getters -> alt+shift+s+r then Alt A then click on ok;</p>\n\n<p>for generating only getters ->alt+shift+s+r then press g then click on ok button;</p>\n\n<p>for generating only setters ->alt+shift+s+r then press l then click on ok button;**</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7291708,
      "reputation" : 3651,
      "user_id" : 5557885,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 54,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dcd35bbb6ab04c49bc1ee792e50ad1f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "rajadilipkolli",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5557885/rajadilipkolli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1489128859,
    "last_edit_date" : 1489128859,
    "creation_date" : 1470412351,
    "answer_id" : 38793287,
    "question_id" : 7221691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>There is an open source jar available know as <a href=\"https://projectlombok.org\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Lombok</a> ,  you just add jar and then annotate your POJO with <a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/features/GetterSetter.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">@Getter &amp; @Setter</a> it will create getters and setters automatically.</p>\n\n<p>Apart from this we can use other features like <a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/features/ToString.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">@ToString</a> ,<a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/features/EqualsAndHashCode.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">@EqualsAndHashCode</a> and pretty other cool stuff which removes vanilla code from your application</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 184347,
      "reputation" : 1293,
      "user_id" : 420343,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c11fb2501ae0b7592be95e7bbbceaeeb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Vallabha Vamaravelli",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/420343/vallabha-vamaravelli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1496549335,
    "creation_date" : 1496549335,
    "answer_id" : 44350685,
    "question_id" : 7221691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li>Open the class file in Eclipse</li>\n<li>Double click on the class name or highlight it</li>\n<li>Then navigate to Source -> Insert Code</li>\n<li>Click on Getter and Setter</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>It opens a popup to select the fields for which getter/setter methods to be generated. Select the fields and click on \"Generate\" button.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/XPUZl.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/XPUZl.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/hPm6P.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/hPm6P.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1341993,
      "reputation" : 2737,
      "user_id" : 1283501,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 74,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c3c3fe58426ff963e60ad87f311e6b2c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Wolf359",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1283501/wolf359"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1523484803,
    "creation_date" : 1523484803,
    "answer_id" : 49785155,
    "question_id" : 7221691,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use Project Lombok or better Kotlin for your Pojos.</p>\n\n<p>(Also, to add Kotlin to your resume ;) )</p>\n\n<p>This :</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class BaseVO {\n    protected Long id;\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean equals(Object obj) {\n        if (obj == null || id == null)\n            return false;\n\n        if (obj instanceof BaseVO)\n            return ((BaseVO) obj).getId().equals(id);\n\n        return false; \n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public int hashCode() {\n        return id == null ? null : id.hashCode();\n    }\n    // getter setter here\n}\n\npublic class Subclass extends BaseVO {\n    protected String name;\n    protected String category;\n    // getter setter here\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>would become this :</p>\n\n<pre><code>open class BaseVO(var id: Long? = null) {\n\n    override fun hashCode(): Int {\n        if (id != null)\n            return id.hashCode()\n\n        return super.hashCode()\n    }\n\n    override fun equals(other: Any?): Boolean {\n        if (id == null || other == null || other !is BaseVO)\n            return false\n\n        return id.hashCode() == other.id?.hashCode()\n    }\n}\n\n@Suppress(\"unused\")\nclass Subclass(\n        var name: String? = null,\n        var category: String? = null\n) : BaseVO()\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or use Kotlin's \"data\" classes. You end up writing even fewer lines of code.</p>\n"
  }, {
